{"word":"ἐξεγείρω","slug":"ἐξεγείρω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξεγείρω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ερῶ</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to awaken</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be awaked, wake up</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:syncopated'>syncop.</a> aor2 <el>ἐξηγρόμην</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; epic 3rd <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>ἐξέγροντο</el> <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>; <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> 2 <el>ἐξεγρήγορα</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to raise from the dead</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to awake, arouse, bring on</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}